        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 5:17PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Palo Duro Canyon, or 15 miles east of Canyon, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Palo Duro Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
